notes.body:
Hi, What is going on with my order, Pls respond the below questions,

1, why the delivery is late. Your timeline also ended yesterday. Yesterday
I complained you with an email regarding this. Today morning i spoke to
pharmeasy customer support asking to cancel the order, i ask for an
immediate refund because i need to buy the same product  from some other
site.

2. Pharmeasy people mentioned in the app that shiprocket is the courier
company handling my product.. But no bodody is sharing the exact reason for
the order delay.. They are saying only technical issue.. What is this..
Dont you have specific reason for delay..

3. Pharmeasy taking orders, seller processing the order, then logistic
processing the order.. But there is no communication between each other.
What is this.. How you are doing business i don't know.. If you have
communication between each other the problem should not be happen to me

4, There is no live tracking updates in pharmeasy.

5. Pharmeasy mentioned shiprocket is the courier. But when I searched in
shiprocket website it is always showing that pickup error and in the same
page below mentioned it as shadowfax.. Order received, location krishna..I
can't understand why shiprocket and shadowfax came in shiprocket website.

6. Regarding my order total order details are all confused and
misinterpreted to customer. Ultimately customer facing the problem.. It is
completely irresponsible and you people dont bother about customer
problems. Customer support asking me to wait for refund. why i need to wait
for my refund, you people failed to deliver my product within your
timeline. is that your mistake or my mistake..then why I need to wait. I
paid and buy your product right. Will Pharmeasy agree to send product to
customer when customer wants to pay later or after 2 days. So don't play
with customers

Pls let me answer all the above questions.. I suffered a lot by booking
order in pharmeasy..

Tracking id : SF1603460431SRF
Order-id : 657607950642479104

Regards
Srivalli.

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Team,

I am writing this email with extreme disappointment and frustration
regarding the handling of my pregnancy test and the repeated failure of
your support team to assist me.

My urine sample was collected on *15th at 6:30 AM*, and I was clearly
promised that the report would be delivered *within 23 hours*. However, as
of now, I have *not received the report*, nor any meaningful update. The
order status is still showing *“On the way to lab,”* which is highly
concerning given the time elapsed.

Since yesterday, I have contacted your customer support *multiple times*.
Each time, I was given vague assurances that the report would be delivered
“soon” or *by today 6:30 AM at the latest*, none of which have been
fulfilled.

Today alone, I called your support team *five times*:

   -

   I was informed that a complaint had been raised, but no resolution
   followed.
   -

   I explicitly requested to speak with a *senior representative* and was
   assured of a callback, which *never happened*.
   -

   During my *5th call*, I was kept on hold for *15 minutes*, after which
   the call was *disconnected without any explanation*. This is completely
   unacceptable and extremely unprofessional.

This situation has caused me significant mental stress, especially
considering that this is a *time-sensitive and critical medical test*.

I need *immediate clarity* on the following:

   1.

   What exactly has happened to my urine sample?
   2.

   Where is the sample currently located?
   3.

   Why is it taking so long to reach or be processed at the lab?
   4.

   Why am I not receiving callbacks despite repeated assurances?
   5.

   Has my sample been misplaced or lost?

The lack of transparency, accountability, and proper communication from
PharmEasy is deeply disappointing. I request *urgent escalation*, a *clear
explanation*, and a *confirmed timeline* for when I will receive my report.

If this issue is not resolved immediately, I will be compelled to escalate
this matter further.

Order ID: *6266124*

Awaiting your immediate response.

Regards,
DEVIKA K D
7356112167

--

helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Dear PharmEasy Team,
I am writing this email with extreme disappointment and frustration regarding the handling of my pregnancy test and the repeated failure of your support team to assist me.
My urine sample was collected on 15th at 6:30 AM, and I was clearly promised that the report would be delivered within 23 hours. However, as of now, I have not received the report, nor any meaningful update. The order status is still showing “On the way to lab,” which is highly concerning given the time elapsed.
Since yesterday, I have contacted your customer support multiple times. Each time, I was given vague assurances that the report would be delivered “soon” or by today 6:30 AM at the latest, none of which have been fulfilled.
Today alone, I called your support team five times:
  • I was informed that a complaint had been raised, but no resolution followed.
  • I explicitly requested to speak with a senior representative and was assured of a callback, which never happened.
  • During my 5th call, I was kept on hold for 15 minutes, after which the call was disconnected without any explanation. This is completely unacceptable and extremely unprofessional.
This situation has caused me significant mental stress, especially considering that this is a time-sensitive and critical medical test.
I need immediate clarity on the following:
  1. What exactly has happened to my urine sample?
  2. Where is the sample currently located?
  3. Why is it taking so long to reach or be processed at the lab?
  4. Why am I not receiving callbacks despite repeated assurances?
  5. Has my sample been misplaced or lost?
The lack of transparency, accountability, and proper communication from PharmEasy is deeply disappointing. I request urgent escalation, a clear explanation, and a confirmed timeline for when I will receive my report.
If this issue is not resolved immediately, I will be compelled to escalate this matter further.
Order ID: 6266124
Awaiting your immediate response.
Regards,
DEVIKA K D

Due to this condition, the doctor did not prescribe the medicine and kept the order on hold. We advised him to consult a doctor and reorder the medicine by uploading a valid prescription. The customer agreed, and hence the order was cancelled.

Hi Team,

As checked in the call recording, the doctor called and consulted the customer. The customer informed the doctor that he has diabetes and had ordered an ED medicine. Due to this condition, the doctor did not prescribe the medicine and kept the order on hold.

 The product quality is not good and it appears to be spoiled,hence it is not safe to use on skin. 
   
 As informed by your customer care team, there is a difference between my previous order and the new order, even though i have reorder the same product from my previous order.
